# docs/plans/ — Implementation Plans

This directory holds implementation plans that agents (or developers) can
pick up and execute. Each file is one self-contained plan.

**Important:** Files in this directory are agent work artifacts — agentify
never overwrites them. Only this README.md is maintained by agentify.

## How Agents Use This Directory

1. Read the relevant plan file completely before writing any code
2. Update the `status:` frontmatter field as work progresses
3. Add findings or blockers under "Notes / Blockers" as you go
4. When complete, update status to `complete`

## File Naming Convention

`YYYY-MM-DD-short-slug.md`

Examples: `2026-06-01-add-oauth-provider.md`, `2026-05-15-refactor-api-layer.md`

## Plan File Format

```markdown
---
title: "Short descriptive title"
status: draft | ready | in-progress | blocked | complete
created: YYYY-MM-DD
updated: YYYY-MM-DD
assignee: (agent or developer name, optional)
---

## Goal

One paragraph: what this plan achieves and why.

## Context

What the agent needs to know before starting. Link to relevant docs:
- Architecture: docs/OVERVIEW.md
- Component being changed: docs/{component}.md
- Related spec (if any): docs/specs/{spec-file}.md

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Criterion 1 (testable, specific)
- [ ] Criterion 2 (testable, specific)
- [ ] Criterion 3 (testable, specific)

## Steps

1. Step one — specific action with file path if applicable
2. Step two — specific action
3. Step three — specific action

## Notes / Blockers

(Add findings, decisions, and blockers here as work progresses)
```

## Status Lifecycle

`draft` → `ready` → `in-progress` → `complete` (or `blocked` if stuck)
